  "What is 'factoring' in algebra?": "",
  "Writing an expression as a product of simpler expressions": "",
  "Multiplying two expressions together": "",
  "Finding the decimal form of a fraction": "",
  "Solving an equation for x": "",
  "Factoring is the process of rewriting an expression as a product of its factors, essentially the reverse of expanding or distributing.": "",
  "What does it mean to 'rationalize the denominator'?": "",
  "Convert the expression to a decimal": "",
  "Make the denominator equal to 1": "",
  "Remove all variables from the denominator": "",
  "Eliminate radical expressions from the denominator": "",
  "Rationalizing the denominator means rewriting a fraction so the denominator contains no radical (square root, cube root, etc.) expressions.": "",
  "What is the 'greatest common factor' (GCF) of a polynomial?": "",
  "The largest expression that divides evenly into every term of the polynomial": "",
  "The constant term of the polynomial": "",
  "The leading coefficient of the polynomial": "",
  "The smallest factor shared by all terms": "",
  "The GCF is the largest factor (including coefficients and variables) that divides into every term of the polynomial without a remainder.": "",
  "What is a 'rational expression'?": "",
  "A polynomial with rational coefficients": "",
  "Any expression involving integers": "",
  "A fraction where numerator and denominator are polynomials": "",
  "An expression that always produces rational numbers": "",
  "A rational expression is a ratio (fraction) of two polynomials, such as (x² + 1)/(x − 3).": "",
  "What does the term 'difference of squares' refer to?": "",
  "An expression of the form a² − b², which factors as (a + b)(a − b)": "",
  "Subtracting two square roots": "",
  "An expression of the form a² + b²": "",
  "Any quadratic with two terms": "",
  "A difference of squares is a binomial of the form a² − b² that factors into the product (a + b)(a − b).": "",
  "What is the 'least common denominator' (LCD) when adding rational expressions?": "",
  "The smallest denominator among all the fractions": "",
  "Always the product of all denominators": "",
  "The product of the numerators": "",
  "The simplest expression that is a multiple of every denominator": "",
  "The LCD is the least common multiple of all denominators, providing the simplest shared denominator for combining fractions.": "",
