  "A trinomial with three squared terms": "",
  "A trinomial whose coefficients are all perfect squares": "",
  "A trinomial of the form a² ± 2ab + b² that factors as (a ± b)²": "",
  "Any trinomial that can be factored": "",
  "A perfect square trinomial has the form a² + 2ab + b² = (a + b)² or a² − 2ab + b² = (a − b)².": "",
  "What does 'conjugate' mean in the context of radicals?": "",
  "The negative of the expression": "",
  "The same expression with the opposite sign between terms (e.g., a + √b becomes a − √b)": "",
  "The square of the expression": "",
  "The reciprocal of the expression": "",
  "The conjugate of a binomial expression with a radical changes the sign between the two terms, so the conjugate of (a + √b) is (a − √b). Multiplying conjugates eliminates the radical.": "",
